@ygalblum reping

I wonder if we have to keep a list of systemd specifiers that expand to and absolute path and the one that are just a name in which case we need to keep the relative path?
Or maybe rethinking the whole thing, would it be smarter to let qualdet not expend the relative path and set `WorkingDirectory=` instead, then podman would resolve the path at runtime which may be better?
